Package com.hotels.beans.generator.core.mapping

Class MappingCode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hotels.beans.generator.core.mapping.MappingCode
  • public abstract class MappingCode
extends Object
    This is the base class for modeling the code block that maps a source object to a destination object. Subclasses must provide an implementation of creation() and initialization() methods, to create mapping code specialized for different kinds of source and destination.

      • creation

        protected abstract com.squareup.javapoet.CodeBlock creation()
        Creation code statement, models the instantiation of the destination type. Implementing classes must know how to create an instance of the destination type. By convention the instance identifier must be "destination".
        Returns:
        the code block

      • initialization

        protected abstract com.squareup.javapoet.CodeBlock initialization()
        Initialization code block, models the mapping between the source and destination types. Implementing classes must know which properties to map, how to access values from both types, and how to apply transformations. By convention the instance identifiers must be "source" and "destination".
        Returns:
        the code block

      • returning

        protected com.squareup.javapoet.CodeBlock returning()
        Returning code statement, models the returning of the destination instance. Implementing classes usually do not need to override this method, unless they have a particular reason. By convention the instance identifier must be "destination".
        Returns:
        the code block
